</p><p>
Other countries already have limits on marking-up essential foods and on changing prices.  But that doesn't stop all price-gouging:  IIRC, during a banana shortage, retail prices in one country were US$8/kilo while the wholesale price barely changed.  (Wholesale price was set months before the shortage happened, and farmers have to sell, they have no leverag</p></div>
